          "body": "Three times the chapter declares that the saints receive the kingdom (7:18, 22, 27). This is not a separate kingdom from the Son of Man's; it is the same kingdom shared. The Son of Man receives dominion in 7:14; the saints receive it in 7:27, and *His kingdom* is *an everlasting kingdom* in which *all the dominions will serve and obey Him* (7:27). The grammar deliberately fuses the two. The chapter that began with four winds stirring the sea ends with the saints of the Most High possessing the kingdom forever, for all ages to come. The persecuted minority of 7:21 is the ruling majority of 7:27. The same God who allowed the saints to be *given into his hand* (7:25) gives the kingdoms into their hand (7:27). This is the chapter's pastoral signature — and Daniel's response is not triumphalism but a pale face and a heart that keeps the matter to itself (7:28). The vision is glorious; the cost of waiting for it is real."
